complex addition and multiplication.
Let
 <m>a,b</m> be real numbers and let <m>z,w</m> be complex
numbers. Show that the following relationships
hold.
  <mdn>
    <mrow xml:id="addextends">a+b \;\;\text{(complex sum)}  \amp = a+b \;\;\text{(real sum)}</mrow>
    <mrow xml:id="multextends">ab \;\;\text{(complex product)}  \amp = ab \;\;\text{(real product)}</mrow>
<mrow xml:id="normextends">
  |a| \;\;\text{(complex norm)}  \amp = |a| \;\;\text{(real absolute value)}</mrow>
<mrow xml:id="normdistovermult">  |zw|  \amp = |z||w| </mrow>
<mrow xml:id="multidentity">  1z  \amp = z1 = z </mrow>
  </mdn>
       </p>
       <p><alert>Comments on this exercise.</alert>
	 <xref ref="addextends"/>, <xref ref="multextends"/>,
and <xref ref="normextends"/> say
   that complex addition, multiplication, and norm <em>extend</em>
    the corresponding
operations on the reals. <xref ref="multidentity"/> is expressed by saying 1 is the 
    <em>(complex) multiplicative identity</em>.</p>
   </statement>
